experiment: F-EXP10: outcome feedback activation via archive reading
hypothesis: Wiring SWARM-LANES-ARCHIVE.md into dispatch_optimizer.py activates outcome feedback for 10+ domains (was 1)

method.description: dispatch_optimizer.py _get_domain_outcomes() only read SWARM-LANES.md (44 lanes). Archive has 265 additional lanes. Fix: read both files.
method.change: Added LANES_ARCHIVE constant and modified _get_domain_outcomes to iterate both files

key_findings.archive_blindness: 265 lanes (86% of history) were invisible to outcome feedback. The mechanism was wired S344 but effectively dormant for 8 sessions.
key_findings.merge_rate_variation: 10x range: nk-complexity 76% vs brain 45% vs governance 33%. Dispatch was treating all as equivalent.
key_findings.lesson_yield_variation: nk-complexity produces 11L from 17 MERGED vs brain 4L from 11 MERGED. Quality varies 2x even among active domains.
key_findings.f_exp1_cross_link: F-EXP1 asks if scoring > random. Answer: the one-shot norm (S327) drove merge rate from 8% to 100%. Scoring drives WHERE sessions go, not WHETHER they succeed. Scoring improvement is selection quality, not completion quality.

expect: Archive reading activates outcome labels for 10+ domains
actual: CONFIRMED: 1 â†’ 8 domains with labels. 2 PROVEN, 3 MIXED, 3 STRUGGLING. Score rankings shifted. Brain penalty largest (-6.1).
diff: Expected 10+, got 8. 34 domains still NEW (n<3). Full activation requires ~100 more DOMEX lanes across dormant domains.
